// place-farm.ipt
// =====================================================================
// A farm / homestead. The farmer, what's grown or raised, the land
// and its state, the household and hands, current activity, and a
// hook. Farms are where the mundane meets the strange — failed crops,
// things in the fields, missing livestock.
//
// Entry table: [@TF-Farm]
//
// Inputs (optional, via API promptValues):
//   prompt1 town  /  prompt2 shopType (display)  /  prompt3 shopName
//
// Reuses people.ipt. No prices.

Title: Farm
Use: people.ipt

Prompt: town {} an unnamed town
Prompt: shopType {} farm
Prompt: shopName {} 

Table: TF-Farm
Set: town={$prompt1}
Set: passedName={$prompt3}
Set: farmer=[@PersonName]
Set: fanc=[@Ancestry]
**[@FarmTitle]** *(farmland near {$town})*\n&
**[@FarmType], [@FarmState]**\n&
**Farmer:** {$farmer}, a [@PersonDesc] {$fanc} who is [@Personality].\n&
**Working the land:** [@FarmProduce]\n&
**The household:** [@FarmHousehold]\n&
**Right now:** [@FarmActivity]\n&
**Worth noting:** [@FarmHook]

Table: FarmTitle
[when]{$passedName}=[do][@FarmName][else]{$passedName}[end]

Table: FarmName
[@FamilyName] Farm
[@FamilyName]'s Holding
The [@FarmNameWord] Farmstead

Table: FarmNameWord
Hollow
Green
Far
Old
Stone
Brook
Hill
Long

Table: FarmType
A prosperous freehold with fat fields and full barns
A hardscrabble tenant farm scraping by on poor soil
A sprawling estate farm worked by many hands
A modest family homestead, just enough and no more
A specialist farm known across the district for one thing
A struggling holding one bad harvest from ruin

Table: FarmState
the crops coming in well and spirits high
the fields parched and the farmer watching the sky
freshly recovered from a blight or pest
worked to exhaustion to meet the lord's tithe
half-fallow, with more land than hands to work it
oddly bountiful this year, more than the soil should give

Table: FarmProduce
fields of wheat and rye, and a kitchen garden
a dairy herd and good cheese
sheep on the hill pastures, wool and mutton
pigs, geese, and a famously bad-tempered goat
orchards heavy with fruit and a cider press
root crops, and bees in a row of white hives

Table: FarmHousehold
{!n=={3+1d4}}the farmer, {$n} family, and [@FarmHelp]

Table: FarmHelp
a couple of hired hands at harvest time
an old dog and a sharp-eyed grandmother who misses nothing
seasonal labourers who come and go with the work
a half-grown brood of children underfoot everywhere
a quiet drifter taken on for room and board
no help at all — they do it all themselves, and it shows

Table: FarmActivity
the whole household is in the fields, racing the weather
a beast has got loose and everyone's chasing it
the farmer is mending a fence and grumbling about neighbours
bread is baking and the smell carries down the lane
a cart is being loaded for market at dawn
the family is at a tense supper, an argument paused for the stranger

Table: FarmHook
livestock has been going missing, and the tracks aren't a wolf's
the farmer ploughed up something old and is afraid to say what
a field refuses to grow anything, in a perfect circle
the household is hiding someone in the hayloft
the harvest is impossibly early, and the farmer won't meet your eye
strangers have offered to buy the land, and won't take no
something comes out of the treeline at night to take the animals
the well water has turned foul and the family is quietly sickening

// Standalone name roll (collision-proof, for note titles etc.).
Table: TF-FarmName
[@FarmName]
